examples.korean: The U.S. education system offers a unique learning experience through what are known as magnet schools. 발음듣기 미국의 교육 시스템은 마그넷 스쿨이라고 알려진 학교를 통해 특별한 교육의 경험을 제공합니다. TIMES CORE
examples.english: The U.S. education system offers a unique learning experience through what are known as magnet schools. 발음

examples.korean: With more than 1.2 million students enrolled, more and more families are discovering the advantages of magnet schools. 발음듣기 120만명 이상의 학생들이 이미 등록되어 있고, 점차적으로 더 많은 가족들이 마그넷 스쿨의 장점을 발견하고 있습니다. TIMES CORE
examples.english: With more than 1.2 million students enrolled, more and more families are discovering the advantages of magnet schools. 발음

examples.korean: Magnet school students are still taught a complete range of subjects. 발음듣기 마그넷 스쿨의 학생들은 여전히 완전한 범위의 과목을 배웁니다. TIMES CORE
examples.english: Magnet school students are still taught a complete range of subjects. 발음

examples.korean: Unfortunately, most magnet schools are able to only accept up to 20 percent of their applicants. 발음듣기 불행하게도, 거의 대부분의 마그넷 학교는 지원자의 20%까지만 받을 수 있습니다. TIMES CORE
examples.english: Unfortunately, most magnet schools are able to only accept up to 20 percent of their applicants. 발음
